# escapement config
.escapement.edn
# Escapement per-session work-dir (transcripts, checkpoints, artifacts)
.escapement/

# Ouroboros sessions — EXCLUDED ENTIRELY from git. The λ conversation
# (checkpointed :messages) is PRE-APPROVAL observation: filesystem-local,
# read by ouroboros.session/curator directly (never via git), and promoted
# into mementum/ only through the human-gated proposal path. Keeping sessions/
# out of git hardens that boundary (git ≡ approved memory/knowledge only).
sessions/

# Experiment RESULTS are machine observation (suites in experiments/ are
# TRACKED — the lab notebook; results promote to the suite's :experiment/verdict
# + knowledge pages through the human gate, like sessions/ → mementum/).
experiments/results/

# Signals — the inter-agent DATA plane (design/signals.md): typed durable
# EDN facts, one file per signal. Machine observation, pre-approval — the
# sessions/ pattern: filesystem-side, queried via the EQL veneer, promoted
# into mementum/ only through the human gate. Git stays approved-memory-only.
# ROOT-ANCHORED (/signals/) — an unanchored signals/ swallows the SOURCE dir
# src/ouroboros/signals/ (caught live at first git status).
/signals/

# Gene score side-store — high-churn machine observation keyed by gene name
# (design/gene-db.md: scores side-stored, joined at query via :gene/scores;
# settled summaries PROMOTE into the tracked gene file through the human gate).
scores/

# The human's private scratch pad — standing instruction: NEVER commit,
# never read unless asked. Ignored so a blind `git add` can't catch it.
human_ideas.md

# Local editor / OS noise
.clj-kondo/
.lsp/
.DS_Store
